        "lastUpdated": 1783455488519,
        "otherAdvice": "<p>Snowy Mountains Highway: open.</p><p>Updates about the road condition throughout the Alpine Season will be provided as the conditions change.</p><p><strong>Chains must be carried </strong>in Kosciuszko National Park in winter (4WD/AWDs exempt). It is recommended that all vehicles carry chains when driving in alpine areas.</p><p>All motorists should be prepared and equipped for sudden changes in road and weather conditions in Alpine areas.</p><p>Motorists should:</p><ul><li>Exercise caution and drive to the conditions at all times</li><li>Drive with headlights on low beam during the daytime and turn on fog lights in times of low visibility</li><li>Obey signage</li><li>Allow extra travel timeChanis required from Sawyers Hut to Kiandra.  Icy stretches Sawyers Hut to Yarrangobilly Caves open</li></ul>",
